2 years really has flown by since I released “Make Me” the music video, with @briannemari as my director. Some things have changed - I moved out of my mom’s house, celebrated two years vegan, became a contracted content creator with two companies, and finished writing/recording a 14-track album. And some things remain the same - still fighting with my anxiety, and my adhd, I still struggle to make ends meet while I make music, and I still don’t know if this will work out the way I had hoped when I was a kid, but the most important thing that remains the same is that I keep working towards it every day, one step at a time.

During the pandemic, with live shows floundering, I continued practicing my craft online, mainly performing through live streams. Having just toured the east and west coasts, I was content at the time with taking a mini break from traveling, and the financial/physical cost of the road. After a few months, however, I began itching to perform live again. Turning my attention to which I was lacking artistically, like music videos, live studio performances, and writing “Trash,” the album, helped me pass the time. 2023 is different though -
I’m making it my business to seek out live performance opportunities, and my second of the year is April 29th at @theviperroom 
DM me for tickets and info!

I think I’m inherently a people pleaser. The thought of disappointing others floods my body with a feeling of warm guilt. I’ve shifted my personal and career choices over the years to avoid negative feedback from family, friends & strangers. What I’ve found is that opinions continue to flow, both positive and negative. Decisions I’ve made to avoid negative feedback from one party morph into disappointment from an opposing party, or worse,
myself. You can’t please everyone, and if you try, you won’t please anyone. Listen to the opinions of others, digest them and allow them to shape your independent choices.
Making choices only to gain allegiance from others will leave you alone. 

#trash #listen #digest #letgo

Make Mango Chia Pudding with me! 🥭 

Chia pudding is one of my favorite high protein snacks. Like mango, chia seeds are great for gut health + have loads of antioxidants, omega 3’s & fiber. Put them together, and what have you got? Bibbidi Bobbidi BOMB chia pudding. Serve with a side of “Mangos” by Lauren Torres for a full, balanced breaky😋

Directions:
- Cut 1/4 of one mango into cubes 
- Cut remaining mango and purée 

- In a bowl, combine:
• 1/2 cups chia seeds
• 2 cups coconut milk 
• 4 tbsp agave (or sweetener of choice)
•Mango purée 

- Whisk & refrigerate until thick 
-Top with cubed mangos & enjoy! 🥭
 
#mangos #chia #chiapudding #vegan #veganfood #newmusic #newsong #rnb #foodporn #trash

Make Mango Ice Cream With Me! 🥭🍦

A delicious way to round out summer & just 4 simple ingredients 🤤 top with the remaining mango pieces and serve with a side of “Mangos” by Lauren Torres 😋
:
• One Mango (cut and frozen) [keep the core for our next vid]
• One 13.5 Oz can Coconut Milk
• 1/2 Cup Maple Syrup (or sweetener or choice)
• 1/2 Teaspoon Vanilla Extract
* blend all of your ingredients together in high speed blender
* in a freezer safe container, freeze the mixture for roughly 4 hours, stirring every 45 mins
**can also use an ice cream maker, but I didn’t. 

#mangos #mango #mangoicecream #vegan #veganfood #veganrecipes #newmusic #stream #spotify #applemusic #linkinbio #rnb #rnbsinger #newsingle

Make Mango Seed Body Butter with me! 🥭🧴

Okay y’all, I said it was happening, so here it is 😍
• With a dull knife, start by cutting into the side of the mango until you begin prying it open to reveal the seed inside. 
(If it takes you a bit of cutting and prying, don’t worry, keep going!) 
• Once the seed is out of the pit, grind it up into a fine powder (@creative_explained used a coffee grinder, I used a food processor)
• Submerge the seed powder in melted coconut oil (I also included melted cocoa butter)
• Refrigerate for an hour or so
• Use on Body, Hair and Scalp
* While making, check out the new single, “Mangos” by Lauren Torres 😉
The original video is credited to @creative_explained

Make “Lullaby” Tea With Me! ☕️🫖 
Fun fact: my upcoming project, “Trash” features a song titled “Lullaby II” as an ode to my very first single, “Lullaby”
So today we’re making a relaxing tea, perfect for when anxiety or stress sets in. If you’re like me, a cup of this concoction may become a daily ritual

Combine:
1 tsp dried chamomile 
1/2 tsp dried lavender 
1/2 tsp dried mint (I used spearmint) 
1 cup boiling water
Steep for 5-10 mins, strain & enjoy with a side of “Lullaby” by Lauren Torres 💤

Trash TV - Ep. 1 🗑️📺 (3 Ways to Reuse An Orange Peel)
1. Place a 1-inch piece of orange peel into your brown sugar to prevent hardening
2. Rub the peel directly onto your skin. The oils help repel those pesky mosquitos
3. Throw the peel directly into your soil to promote growth. 

Some additional ideas I didn’t include in the video: 
- Candied Orange Peels (tasty snack)
- Potpourri Stove Pot with Orange Peel + Cinnamon Stick (smells so good)
- Throw a small piece of peel in your garbage disposal to keep it smelling fresh. 
Whatever you do, don’t throw it away! 😉 

#trashtv #trash #orange #reuse #sustainability #sustainable #sustainableliving #ep1 #singer #songwriter #newmusic #comingsoon

Trash Tv - Ep. 2: Make Scrap Apple Cider Vinegar with me! 🍎🍏
• Fill a clean, wide mouth jar with your leftover apple cores
• In a separate jar, dissolve 1 tablespoon sugar per 1 cup filtered water (make enough to submerge the apple cores)
• Wrap a breathable towel or flour sack over the jar and secure with a rubber band (this time, I used a disposable garlic sack)
•Place somewhere dry & dark for 2 weeks, stirring daily
•After two weeks, strain and compost the apple cores. What’s left is scrap apple cider vinegar, perfect for cleaning, cooking, and even revitalizing hair rinses. Listen to a little “Trash” by Lauren Torres for some inspo😘

#trash #scrap #applecidervinegar #apple #applecider #homemade #repurposed #repurpose #reuse #newmusic #comingsoon #laurentorres

Trash TV, Ep. 3: 2 Ways to Reuse Coffee Grounds

1. Fertilize & debug your plants: coffee grounds contain essential nutrients for plant growth including, nitrogen, calcium & potassium. They also contain caffeine and diterpenes, which are deterrents from mosquitos, fruit flies and beetles

2. Mix 1 part coffee grounds with 1 part water and use on face and scalp for a rejuvenating facial or hair rinse 

#trashtv #trash #reuse #coffeegrounds #repurpose #fertilizer #exfoliant #howto

Trash TV, Episode 4: Make Pineapple Peel Tea With Me! 🍍🍵
Did you know you can use every part of a pineapple, including it’s peel, core and crown? 
First, let’s make Pineapple Peel Tea! This tea is great for aiding digestion and has anti-inflammatory properties 
Start by soaking your pineapple peel and core in vinegar for roughly 30 mins, then combine in a large pot:
• Clean Peel + Core from 1 Pineapple
• 1 Cinnamon Stick
• 1-inch Knob of Ginger
• 1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder 
• 1.5 tbsp Maple Syrup (or sweetener of choice)
• 6 Cups Water
* Boil for 30 mins-1 hour, Strain Tea, Compost remaining ingredients and enjoy hot or cold!
 *(This recipe has been adapted from the recipe by @plantyou for pineapple skin tea, to extract a little more tea) 
To Plant Pineapple Crown:
Twist the Pineapple Crown (Top of Pineapple) and Pull to Remove. Place in Fresh Soil, and a new pineapple will sprout in 18-24 months. 🍍 

#trash #trashtv #pineapple #tea #pineapplepeeltea #howto #plants #plantbased #plant #grow #growyourown #reuse #repurpose #dontthrowitaway #singer #singersongwriter #newmusic #comingsoon #trashalbum

Trash TV, Episode 5🗑️📺: Make a detoxifying hair rinse out of your scrap apple cider vinegar 🍏🍎 (See Episode 3)
What you’ll need: 
-2 Cups Scrap Apple Cider Vinegar (or store bought) 
-A few handfuls of your choice of herbs, fresh or dried, 
**I used dried lavender (Increases circulation & promotes hair growth), dried Calendula (Soothes scalp irritation), fresh basil (helps the body eliminate toxins and heavy metals), fresh rosemary (strengthens hair, fights dandruff)
-5 to 10 drops essential oil 
* I used peppermint essential oil (eases mind and body fatigue)
Directions:
•Combine a small handful of each desired flower/herb and 5-10 drops essential oil in a glass jar with apple cider vinegar (ensure herbs are fully submerged) 
•Store in a warm spot and infuse for 4- 6 weeks 
•Strain mixture and compost herbs 
•In a spray bottle, combine 1 part (1/2-1 1/2 cups depending on hair length) infused apple cider vinegar with 5 parts water (for typical scalp), 4 parts water (for oily scalp), or 6 parts water (for dry scalp) 
•use once a week with your normal hair routine for shiny, rejuvenated hair.

Trash TV, Ep. 6 🗑️📺 - 3 Magical Uses For A Banana Peel! 🍌
I had no clue banana peels could be used for so much. These are just some of the many useful ways to repurpose a banana peel before it heads to the trash - 
1. Whiten your teeth 🦷: Yes, according to some research, when using the fleshy part of a banana peel on your teeth for roughly 2 weeks, you may start to see some whitening and stain removing effects take place
2. Shine your shoes: 👞 I tried this one, and I can confidently say those shoes are 10x shinier. Side note - Make sure you have a rag or towel to wipe of the banana fragments 😂 
3. Clean Your Indoor Houseplants 🪴: Yep, you read that right. Wipe the surface dust from your indoor houseplants with the fleshy part the banana peel and reveal a smooth sheen 
(P.S. My new single, “Time” Drops FRIDAY! (Presave the song @ the link In my bio)

The irony is that while filming this music video, in which I sing about having more time, my great Aunt Barbara was diagnosed with, and ultimately succumbed to stage 4 pancreatic cancer. While it’s a blessing to have more time, and I continue to make the most of each passing day, some of us have our time cut short. So, this one is dedicated to you Auntie Barbara, and to every other soul whose passing came too soon. May you rest peacefully. ♥️
